{
  "stem": "1975.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were cut as the war started, right in the beginning.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were no communications.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "No telephone, no [INAUDIBLE], no telegraph, nothing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, I-- I practically didn't know what is happening to my family.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I didn't know what happens to my-- to a few blocks away from us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We tried to stay home as much as possible and to get, little by little, from time to time, out, and to get some supply, some food, because it was very dangerous to get out in the street, because in many cases-- many occasions where the people went out to the street, they-- they would never come back.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We had some relatives on the-- we had a high part of Kaunas, which was the-- the Green Mountains.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That was the name.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And some relatives-- the family of my aunt was married to my-- to my uncle-- lived there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And one of her brothers had a-- a farm.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, at one point, one evening we decided to move out from the place where we're staying and to go to their-- to their house.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And fortunately-- when we came there, we heard terrible things.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were assaulted.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were taken away-- everything-- all the belongings.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they wanted to kill and to take away my aunt's brothers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But fortunately, they had some watches, and they were able to bribe the-- those people who came in.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were completely drunk, you know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's-- you know, Lithuanians, they-- the-- the non-Jews there were at a-- at a-- at a level of-- very low level of-- of intelligence, in a certain way, I would say that, because they were-- many of those-- first of all, drinking was a-- a national-- a national--",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right, pastime.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
